{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775884905424,"sessionID":"ses_28504aafeffeuELUN0vaOSiBwq","part":{"id":"prt_d7afd2b6c001Z6uw4TCMU4OR7Z","messageID":"msg_d7afbde56001hY60GHl0JvwzJI","sessionID":"ses_28504aafeffeuELUN0vaOSiBwq","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-ba3250621c3541fb9fe8c867a6f848c9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-031/delta-spec.md","content":"# Delta Spec: AR-031 вҖ” RBAC й…ҚзҪ®\n\n**Module:** `manifests`  \n**Language:** YAML  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nDefine Kubernetes RBAC resources (ServiceAccount, Role/ClusterRole, RoleBinding/ClusterRoleBinding) for AgentCube components to enable secure, least-privilege access to Kubernetes API resources. Router uses namespace-scoped Role for Secret management; WorkloadManager uses cluster-wide ClusterRole for sandbox lifecycle management and CRD operations.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: Router RBAC template\n\nThe system SHALL provide namespace-scoped RBAC resources for Router with conditional creation and validation.\n\n#### Scenario: Router RBAC conditional rendering\n- **GIVEN** `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml` exists\n- **WHEN** `{{ .Values.router.rbac.create }}` is `true`\n- **THEN** ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding SHALL be rendered\n- **WHEN** value is `false`\n- **THEN** no RBAC resources SHALL be rendered for router\n\n#### Scenario: Router serviceAccountName validation guard\n- **GIVEN** Router RBAC is enabled (`router.rbac.create: true`)\n- **WHEN** `{{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}` is empty or not set\n- **THEN** template SHALL fail with error: `\"router.serviceAccountName must be set when router.rbac.create is true\"`\n- **WHEN** value is set\n- **THEN** template SHALL render successfully\n\n#### Scenario: Router ServiceAccount creation\n- **GIVEN** Router RBAC is enabled\n- **WHEN** ServiceAccount is templated\n- **THEN** ServiceAccount SHALL have:\n  - `apiVersion: v1`\n  - `kind: ServiceAccount`\n  - `name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}`\n  - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n  - `labels` from helper template `agentcube.labels`\n\n#### Scenario: Router Role namespace-scoped permissions\n- **GIVEN** Router needs Secret access within its namespace\n- **WHEN** Role is templated\n- **THEN** Role SHALL have:\n  - `apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1`\n  - `kind: Role`\n  - `name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}`\n  - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n  - `rules` array with single entry:\n    - `apiGroups: [\"\"]` (core API group)\n    - `resources: [\"secrets\"]`\n    - `verbs: [\"get\",\"list\",\"watch\",\"create\",\"update\",\"patch\",\"delete\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: Router RoleBinding binding\n- **GIVEN** Router Role needs binding to ServiceAccount\n- **WHEN** RoleBinding is templated\n- **THEN** RoleBinding SHALL have:\n  - `apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1`\n  - `kind: RoleBinding`\n  - `name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}`\n  - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n  - `labels` from helper template\n  - `subjects`: ServiceAccount with name from values in release namespace\n  - `roleRef`:\n    - `apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io`\n    - `kind: Role`\n    - `name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}`\n\n#### Scenario: Router RBAC no cluster-wide access\n- **GIVEN** Router Role only grants namespace-scoped permissions\n- **WHEN** Role rules are evaluated\n- **THEN** no ClusterRole or ClusterRoleBinding SHALL be created for Router\n- **AND** Router SHALL NOT have access to resources in other namespaces\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: WorkloadManager RBAC template\n\nThe system SHALL provide cluster-wide RBAC resources for WorkloadManager with full CRD operation permissions.\n\n#### Scenario: WorkloadManager ServiceAccount creation\n- **GIVEN** `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` is rendered\n- **WHEN** helm template executes\n- **THEN** ServiceAccount SHALL have:\n  - `apiVersion: v1`\n  - `kind: ServiceAccount`\n  - `name: workloadmanager`\n  - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n  - `labels` from helper template `agentcube.labels`\n\n#### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole agent-sandbox permissions\n- **GIVEN** WorkloadManager needs Sandbox CRD access\n- **WHEN** ClusterRole rules for `agents.x-k8s.io` are defined\n- **THEN** ClusterRole SHALL grant:\n  - `apiGroups: [\"agents.x-k8s.io\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"sandboxes\"]`\n  - `verbs: [\"get\",\"list\",\"watch\",\"create\",\"update\",\"patch\",\"delete\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole sandbox extension permissions\n- **GIVEN** WorkloadManager needs extension CRD access\n- **WHEN** ClusterRole rules for `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` are defined\n- **THEN** ClusterRole SHALL grant:\n  - `apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"sandboxclaims\",\"sandboxtemplates\",\"sandboxwarmpools\"]`\n  - `verbs: [\"get\",\"list\",\"watch\",\"create\",\"update\",\"patch\",\"delete\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"sandboxwarmpools/status\"]`\n  - `verbs: [\"get\",\"update\",\"patch\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole CodeInterpreter permissions\n- **GIVEN** WorkloadManager needs CodeInterpreter CRD access\n- **WHEN** ClusterRole rules for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` are defined\n- **THEN** ClusterRole SHALL grant:\n  - `apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"codeinterpreters\"]`\n  - `verbs: [\"get\",\"list\",\"watch\",\"create\",\"update\",\"patch\",\"delete\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"codeinterpreters/status\"]`\n  - `verbs: [\"get\",\"update\",\"patch\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"codeinterpreters/finalizers\"]`\n  - `verbs: [\"update\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole AgentRuntime permissions\n- **GIVEN** WorkloadManager needs AgentRuntime CRD read access\n- **WHEN** ClusterRole rules for AgentRuntime are defined\n- **THEN** ClusterRole SHALL grant:\n  - `apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"agentruntimes\"]`\n  - `verbs: [\"get\",\"list\",\"watch\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"agentruntimes/status\"]`\n  - `verbs: [\"update\",\"patch\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole core resource permissions\n- **GIVEN** WorkloadManager needs Pod and Secret access\n- **WHEN** ClusterRole rules for core API are defined\n- **THEN** ClusterRole SHALL grant:\n  - `apiGroups: [\"\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"pods\"]`\n  - `verbs: [\"get\",\"list\",\"watch\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"secrets\"]`\n  - `verbs: [\"get\",\"list\",\"watch\",\"create\",\"update\",\"patch\",\"delete\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole TokenReview permission\n- **GIVEN** WorkloadManager needs TokenReview for authentication\n- **WHEN** ClusterRole rules for authentication API are defined\n- **THEN** ClusterRole SHALL grant:\n  - `apiGroups: [\"authentication.k8s.io\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"tokenreviews\"]`\n  - `verbs: [\"create\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding creation\n- **GIVEN** WorkloadManager ClusterRole needs binding\n- **WHEN** ClusterRoleBinding is templated\n- **THEN** ClusterRoleBinding SHALL have:\n  - `apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1`\n  - `kind: ClusterRoleBinding`\n  - `name: workloadmanager`\n  - `labels` from helper template\n  - `subjects`:\n    - `kind: ServiceAccount`\n    - `name: workloadmanager`\n    - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n  - `roleRef`:\n    - `apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io`\n    - `kind: ClusterRole`\n    - `name: workloadmanager`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: RBAC values.yaml configuration\n\nThe system SHALL provide configurable RBAC flags in values.yaml.\n\n#### Scenario: Router RBAC create flag default\n- **GIVEN** `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` defines router section\n- **WHEN** `router.rbac.create` is defined\n- **THEN** default value SHALL be `false` (RBAC disabled by default)\n\n#### Scenario: Router serviceAccountName configuration\n- **GIVEN** router RBAC can be enabled\n- **WHEN** `router.serviceAccountName` is defined in values.yaml\n- **THEN** default value SHALL be `\"\"` (empty string, user must set when enabling RBAC)\n\n#### Scenario: Router RBAC enabled deployment\n- **GIVEN** user wants Router RBAC created by Helm\n- **WHEN** values.yaml is configured with:\n  - `router.rbac.create: true`\n  - `router.serviceAccountName: \"agentcube-router\"`\n- **THEN** Helm install SHALL create ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding\n- **AND** Router Deployment SHALL use `serviceAccountName: agentcube-router`\n\n#### Scenario: Router external RBAC deployment\n- **GIVEN** user has pre-existing ServiceAccount/RBAC externally managed\n- **WHEN** values.yaml is configured with:\n  - `router.rbac.create: false`\n  - `router.serviceAccountName: \"my-existing-sa\"`\n- **THEN** Helm install SHALL NOT create RBAC resources\n- **AND** Router Deployment SHALL reference existing ServiceAccount\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: RBAC security compliance\n\nThe system SHALL follow Kubernetes RBAC best practices with minimal permission grants.\n\n#### Scenario: No wildcard permissions\n- **GIVEN** RBAC templates define permission rules\n- **WHEN** ClusterRole or Role rules are inspected\n- **THEN** no rule SHALL use wildcard `\"*\"` for `resources` or `verbs`\n- **AND** all `apiGroups`, `resources`, `verbs` SHALL be explicitly listed\n\n#### Scenario: Least privilege principle\n- **GIVEN** WorkloadManager needs specific operations on resources\n- **WHEN** ClusterRole verbs are defined per resource\n- **THEN** verbs SHALL be minimum required for operation:\n  - Read-only resources: `get`, `list`, `watch` only\n  - Status subresources: `get`, `update`, `patch` only (no delete)\n  - Finalizers: `update` only\n  - Managed resources: full CRUD where lifecycle management required\n\n#### Scenario: Namespace isolation for Router\n- **GIVEN** Router only needs secrets in its own namespace\n- **WHEN** Router Role is evaluated\n- **THEN** Role SHALL NOT grant access to cluster-wide resources\n- **AND** Role SHALL NOT grant access to resources in other namespaces\n- **AND** RoleBinding SHALL only bind within `{{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n\n#### Scenario: TokenReview restricted to WorkloadManager\n- **GIVEN** TokenReview is sensitive authentication operation\n- **WHEN** RBAC permissions are audited\n- **THEN** TokenReview `create` verb SHALL only be granted to WorkloadManager\n- **AND** Router SHALL NOT have TokenReview permission\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: RBAC template validation\n\nThe system SHALL provide template validation for RBAC configuration.\n\n#### Scenario: Helm template rendering validation\n- **GIVEN** RBAC templates are complete\n- **WHEN** `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=agentcube-router` is executed\n- **THEN** output SHALL contain valid YAML for:\n  - Router ServiceAccount\n  - Router Role\n  - Router RoleBinding\n  - WorkloadManager ServiceAccount\n  - WorkloadManager ClusterRole\n  - WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding\n\n#### Scenario: Helm template failure on missing serviceAccountName\n- **GIVEN** Router RBAC is enabled\n- **WHEN** `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set router.rbac.create=true` is executed without `router.serviceAccountName`\n- **THEN** template SHALL fail with error message containing `\"router.serviceAccountName must be set\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Helm template skip when RBAC disabled\n- **GIVEN** Router RBAC is disabled\n- **WHEN** `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set router.rbac.create=false` is executed\n- **THEN** output SHALL NOT contain Router ServiceAccount, Role, or RoleBinding\n- **AND** WorkloadManager RBAC SHALL still be rendered\n\n#### Scenario: Helm lint passes\n- **GIVEN** RBAC templates are complete\n- **WHEN** `helm lint manifests/charts/base` is executed\n- **THEN** lint SHALL pass with no errors related to RBAC templates\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: E2E RBAC validation\n\nThe system SHALL validate RBAC permissions in E2E tests.\n\n#### Scenario: E2E Router secret access\n- **GIVEN** Router RBAC is deployed with `router.rbac.create=true`\n- **WHEN** Router Pod attempts to create/read/update/delete Secret in its namespace\n- **THEN** operations SHALL succeed (permission granted by Role)\n- **WHEN** Router Pod attempts to access Secret in different namespace\n- **THEN** operation SHALL fail (namespace isolation)\n\n#### Scenario: E2E WorkloadManager sandbox creation\n- **GIVEN** WorkloadManager RBAC is deployed\n- **WHEN** WorkloadManager Pod attempts to create Sandbox CRD\n- **THEN** operation SHALL succeed (permission granted by ClusterRole)\n- **WHEN** WorkloadManager Pod attempts to update Sandbox status\n- **THEN** operation SHALL succeed\n\n#### Scenario: E2E WorkloadManager CodeInterpreter lifecycle\n- **GIVEN** WorkloadManager RBAC is deployed\n- **WHEN** WorkloadManager Pod attempts full lifecycle on CodeInterpreter CRD\n- **THEN** create, get, list, update, delete SHALL succeed\n- **WHEN** WorkloadManager Pod attempts to update CodeInterpreter finalizers\n- **THEN** operation SHALL succeed\n\n#### Scenario: E2E WorkloadManager Pod read access\n- **GIVEN** WorkloadManager RBAC is deployed\n- **WHEN** WorkloadManager Pod attempts to get/list/watch Pods\n- **THEN** operations SHALL succeed\n- **WHEN** WorkloadManager Pod attempts to create/delete Pod directly\n- **THEN** operation SHALL fail (only read verbs granted)\n\n---\n\n## Constants Summary\n\n| Constant | Value | File | Purpose |\n|----------|-------|------|---------|\n| `ROUTER_RBAC_CREATE_DEFAULT` | `false` | `values.yaml` | Router RBAC disabled by default |\n| `ROUTER_SA_NAME_DEFAULT` | `\"\"` | `values.yaml` | Router ServiceAccount name must be explicitly set |\n| `WORKLOADMANAGER_SA_NAME` | `workloadmanager` | `rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` | Fixed ServiceAccount name for WorkloadManager |\n| `RBAC_API_VERSION` | `rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1` | RBAC templates | Stable RBAC API version |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies Summary\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `Kubernetes` | `>=1.24` | RBAC API stability (rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1) |\n| `Helm 3` | `>=3.8.0` | Template conditionals and validation guards |\n| `agent-sandbox CRDs` | `agents.x-k8s.io` | Sandbox, SandboxClaim, SandboxTemplate, SandboxWarmPool resources |\n| `AgentCube CRDs` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | CodeInterpreter, AgentRuntime custom resources |\n\n---\n\n## File Changes Summary\n\n| File | Action | Description |\n|------|--------|-------------|\n| `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml` | Modified | Add validation guard for serviceAccountName requirement |\n| `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` | Existing | WorkloadManager RBAC resources (no changes) |\n| `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` | Modified | Document `router.rbac.create` and `router.serviceAccountName` defaults |\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- proposal.md вҖ” AR-031 proposal with scope and implementation checklist\n- manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml вҖ” Router RBAC template\n- manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml вҖ” WorkloadManager RBAC template\n- Kubernetes RBAC Documentation вҖ” https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/access-authn-authz/rbac/\n- changes/AR-030/delta-spec.md вҖ” Helm Chart templates context\n\n---\n\n## Validation Checklist\n\n- [ ] `helm lint manifests/charts/base` passes with no errors\n- [ ] Router RBAC renders when `router.rbac.create=true` with valid `serviceAccountName`\n- [ ] Router RBAC skipped when `router.rbac.create=false`\n- [ ] Template fails when `router.rbac.create=true` without `serviceAccountName`\n- [ ] Router Role only grants Secret permissions (namespace-scoped)\n- [ ] WorkloadManager ClusterRole grants all required CRD permissions\n- [ ] No wildcard (`*`) in any RBAC resources or verbs\n- [ ] TokenReview only granted to WorkloadManager, not Router\n- [ ] WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding references correct ServiceAccount\n- [ ] E2E test: Router can manage secrets in its namespace\n- [ ] E2E test: WorkloadManager can create/manage Sandboxes\n- [ ] E2E test: WorkloadManager can create/manage CodeInterpreters"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml\">\nERROR [1:3] Block collections are not allowed within flow collections\nERROR [1:5] Missing , or : between flow map items\nERROR [2:1] Unexpected flow-map-start at node end\nERROR [2:2] Unexpected flow-map-start at node end\nERROR [2:3] Unexpected seq-item-ind at node end\nERROR [2:5] Unexpected scalar at node end\nERROR [2:46] Unexpected flow-map-end token in YAML stream: \"}\"\nERROR [2:47] Unexpected flow-map-end token in YAML stream: \"}\"\nERROR [3:1] Unexpected flow-map-start token in YAML stream: \"{\"\nERROR [3:2] Unexpected flow-map-start token in YAML stream: \"{\"\nERROR [3:3] Unexpected seq-item-ind token in YAML stream: \"-\"\nERROR [3:5] Unexpected scalar token in YAML stream: \"fail \\\"router.serviceAccountName must be set when router.rbac.create is true\\\"\"\nERROR [3:82] Unexpected flow-map-end token in YAML stream: \"}\"\nERROR [3:83] Unexpected flow-map-end token in YAML stream: \"}\"\nERROR [4:1] Unexpected flow-map-start token in YAML stream: \"{\"\nERROR [4:2] Unexpected flow-map-start token in YAML stream: \"{\"\nERROR [4:3] Unexpected seq-item-ind token in YAML stream: \"-\"\nERROR [4:5] Unexpected scalar token in YAML stream: \"end\"\nERROR [4:9] Unexpected flow-map-end token in YAML stream: \"}\"\nERROR [4:10] Unexpected flow-map-end token in YAML stream: \"}\"\n... and 38 more\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspa